President Obama issued a statement on the celebration of Orthodox Christmas, expressing his well wishes to Orthodox Christians in the United States and worldwide. He emphasized the importance of reflecting on the commandment to love one another as Jesus Christ loved us. The President acknowledged the contributions of Orthodox Christians in strengthening religious and civic bonds and expressed gratitude for their acts of love towards their neighbors. He also reaffirmed the commitment to protect the right of all people to practice their faith and stand in solidarity with communities and congregations that have faced persecution and violent attacks. President Obama concluded by expressing solidarity with Orthodox Christians and joining them in praying and working for peace and justice in the coming year.